LIFE
====

Purpose of this project is to make a useful performance's measurement tool based on the "Game of Life" (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conway%27s_Game_of_Life), suitable on HPC systems.

Compilation - GNU
==================

Serial: gcc   life.c -o life 

OMP:    gcc   life.c --define OMP -fopenmp -o life_omp 

MPI:    mpicc life.c --define MPI -o life_mpi

Hybrid: mpicc life.c --define MPI --define OMP -fopenmp -o life_hybrid

Compilation - INTEL
===================

Serial: icc   life.c -o life 

OMP:    icc   life.c -D OMP -fopenmp -o life_omp 

MPI:    mpicc life.c -D MPI -o life_mpi

Hybrid: mpicc life.c -D MPI -D OMP -fopenmp -o life_hybrid

PLEASE NOTE: to compile on MIC use "-mmic" option.

Compilation - PGI
=================
OMP: pgcc -mp=numa life_double_for.c -DOMP -fast -mp -Minfo -o life_double_for_omp_pgcc


Version History:
================

  13.10.16   Fix vectors alignment (seg. fault on MIC)

  13.10.08   Add vectorized computation

  12.09.14   Adapted for serial version

